## üí° Clinical Notes & Commentary

### Traditional Understanding
Master formula for liver and gallbladder "damp-heat fire" patterns. Long Dan Cao is one of the strongest liver-clearing herbs. The formula balances clearing heat with nourishing blood (Dang Gui, Sheng Di) to prevent over-drying.

### Modern Pharmacology
Research shows hepatoprotective, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial effects. Long Dan Cao contains iridoid glycosides with liver-protective properties. Studies show efficacy in hepatitis, urogenital infections, and inflammatory eye conditions.

### Clinical Experience
Very effective for acute inflammatory conditions affecting liver, gallbladder, and urogenital systems. Often dramatic results within 3-7 days. Must monitor for over-clearing in weak patients.

### Dosage & Administration
**Standard Dose**: Decoct above doses twice daily, or 6-9g granules twice daily
**Preparation**: Standard decoction, don't overcook to preserve active compounds
**Timing**: Between meals, can take 3 times daily for acute conditions
**Duration**: 1-3 weeks for acute conditions, stop when heat clears

